# code-worker rules

you are the code-worker for the goon repo. you build tools from the task board.

## repo structure

```
AGENTS.md                     <- read this first for full context
notes/boards/
  system-board.md             <- mission (read-only for you)
  coding-agent-task-board.md  <- your task queue (you update status here)
notes/daily/                  <- gooner's research (read-only for you)
notes/watchlists/             <- gooner's watchlists (read-only for you)
tools/                        <- YOUR build output goes here
logs/code-worker/             <- YOUR cycle logs go here
hermes/                       <- gooner's agent state (read-only for you)
external-agent/               <- process docs (read for context)
```

## what you do every cycle

1. `git pull origin main`
2. read `notes/boards/coding-agent-task-board.md`
3. pick highest-priority `queued` task (skip `needs_spec`)
4. if a task is already `in_progress` with your cycle stamp, continue it
5. build in `tools/<task-name>/` — README + python code + tests
6. run tests
7. update task status on the board
8. write cycle log to `logs/code-worker/YYYY-MM-DD-HH.md`
9. `git add -A` then commit with prefix `build:` and push

## file ownership

- you OWN: `tools/`, `logs/code-worker/`
- you UPDATE: `notes/boards/coding-agent-task-board.md` (status changes only)
- you READ: everything else
- you NEVER write to: `notes/daily/`, `notes/watchlists/`, `hermes/memories/`

## build conventions

- python preferred, minimal deps
- no LLM API keys available — rule-based implementations first
- every tool gets its own directory: `tools/<tool-name>/`
- every tool directory has: `README.md`, source code, tests
- input/output contracts must match what the task board specifies
- tests must cover the `testable_acceptance` criteria from the task

## commit conventions

- prefix: `build:` for tool work, `tools:` for tool-only file changes
- example: `build: spam-classifier — rule-based v1 with 12 pattern rules`
- one logical change per commit when possible

## task status flow

```
queued -> in_progress (you pick it, add picked_cycle timestamp)
in_progress -> done (tests pass, tool is functional)
in_progress -> blocked (you hit a real blocker, add note)
needs_spec -> (skip — waiting on gooner to provide sample data)
```

## empty cycle policy

- if all tasks are `done`, `needs_spec`, or `blocked`: read gooner's latest daily note for new actionable patterns
- if you find something buildable: add it to the task board and start building
- if nothing actionable: log an idle cycle with reason and stop
- never produce an empty commit or a cycle with zero explanation

## cycle log format

write to `logs/code-worker/YYYY-MM-DD-HH.md`:

```
# code-worker cycle — YYYY-MM-DD HH:00 UTC
- task picked: <name>
- status change: <from> -> <to>
- what was built: <path> — <description>
- tests: <pass count / total>
- commits: <hash>
- blockers: <issues or "none">
- next cycle: <plan>
```
